the publication of Torremuzza 1769",1769,1800,[67,72],{"_":68,"type":69,"ref":70,"region":71},"Drepanum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462187","Sicilia",{"_":73,"type":74,"ref":75,"region":71},"Trapani","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2522876",[77],[78,79],38.0176,12.53617,{"_":81,"type":82,"subtype":83,"geo":20},"Reportedly found in 1768 during work on the Chiesa di San Pietro, Trapani","found","discovered",[],{"_":86,"type":87,"subtype":88,"geo":20},"None","observed","autopsied",{"_":90,"type":91,"subtype":92,"geo":20},"Lost (manuscript copy only)","not-observed","lost",[94],{"n":95,"url":96,"height":97,"width":98,"desc":99,"surfaceType":100},"screen","ISic003556_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front","Sicily",{"_":103,"role":104,"ref":105,"museum":106},"Museo Regionale Agostino Pepoli","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/105",{"slug":107,"type":104,"name":103,"uri":105,"description":108,"location":109},"105","The archaeological collection is housed in one long room that has been subdivided into 4 discrete areas containing 25 cases and a series of open displays. 1 case contains pre- and proto-historic material, 3 are for material from Selinunte, 1 Camarina, 8 Erice, 1 Mozia, 1 Birgi, 1 Lilybaeum, 1 Centuripe, 4 contain material of unknown origin, 1 mixed sites, and then 1 for Punic stamped amphora handles, 1 for Greek and Roman stamped amphora handles, and 1 for Latin epigraphy. In addition there are open displays of material found on the seabed (amphorae, anchor parts, a Roman ram from the Aegadi Islands battle), a large two-sided Latin inscription and a section on Arabic and later Jewish inscriptions",{"settlement":73,"region":73,"country":110,"address":111,"geo":112},"Italy","Via Conte A. Pepoli 180. 91100 - Trapani (TP)",{"lat":113,"lon":114},38.01913,12.541978,[116,119],{